        <briefdescription>
<para>This function runs a self-test on the <ref refid="struct_x_dp" kindref="compound">XDp</ref> driver/device depending on whether the core is operating in TX or RX mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The sanity test checks whether or not all tested registers hold their default reset values.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dp" kindref="compound">XDp</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the self-test passed - all tested registers hold their default reset values.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE otherwise.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
